The paper discusses the implementation of machine learning systems on non-deterministic hardware, which involves the use of digital stochastic circuits for approximating matrix computations. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields, including computer architecture (cs.AR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
